| name = Logan Bartholomew | image = | imagesize = 150 | caption = | birth_name = John Logan Batholomew | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1984|2|9}} | birth_place = [[Galion, Ohio|Galion]], [[Ohio]], [[United States|U.S.]] | other_names = | occupation = [[Actor]] | years_active = 2003-present | website = }} '''John Logan Bartholomew''' (born February 9, 1984) is an [[United States|American]] [[actor]] born in [[Galion, Ohio]], best known for his role of Willie LaHaye in 3 of the 8 films in the ''[[Love Comes Softly]]'' series. He later appeared in series like ''[[CSI: Miami]]'' (2005) and ''[[Close to Home (2005 TV series)|Close to Home]]'' (2007). He also had a small cameo in the popular series Ghost Whisperer. He dreamed of being a baseball player, but when his arm snapped in high school he took acting lessons.
